text.tspan: Child deaths from pneumonia by risk factor, World, 1990 to 2019
Shown is the number of deaths of children younger than five from pneumonia and other lower respiratory diseases by
risk factor that was estimated to be responsible for these deaths.
Indoor air pollution from solid fuels
Data source: IHME, Global Burden of Disease (2019)
Note: Risk factors can interact and overlap for a given cause of death; therefore the sum of deaths attributed to risk factors will exceed the
total number of deaths from pneumonia.
